WEBVTT

1
00:02:19.208 --> 00:02:21.832
<i>September 17th. 1983.</i>

2
00:02:26.166 --> 00:02:28.665
<i>The flat Fon and I got
is really nice.</i>

3
00:02:30.458 --> 00:02:31.915
<i>especially the location.</i>

4
00:02:33.250 --> 00:02:35.832
<i>Eight kilometres from Vigo.
surrounded by the sea.</i>

5
00:02:37.208 --> 00:02:39.874
<i>From the lounge and bedroom.
we can see the Ría.</i>

6
00:02:39.958 --> 00:02:42.249
<i>Cangas. Moaña. the Cíes Islands...</i>

7
00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:43.750
<i>and the sea.</i>

8
00:02:44.875 --> 00:02:47.832
<i>Sometimes it's calm. blue. peaceful.</i>

9
00:02:47.916 --> 00:02:50.290
<i>Sometimes wild. choppy.</i>

10
00:02:50.375 --> 00:02:51.665
<i>but always the sea.</i>

11
00:04:05.708 --> 00:04:08.582
Day 1:
July 16. 2004

12
00:04:08.666 --> 00:04:15.749
Will I find a trace
of my biological parents?

13
00:04:33.166 --> 00:04:34.290
What are you doing?

14
00:04:36.583 --> 00:04:37.999
Hey. we're not finished!

15
00:05:05.083 --> 00:05:07.332
CIVIL REGISTRY

16
00:05:17.583 --> 00:05:22.124
Look. I've found Alfonso Piñeiro.
but not on the date you said.

17
00:05:22.666 --> 00:05:25.165
- Check if this is him.
- Yes.

18
00:05:26.708 --> 00:05:28.040
Yes. it's him.

19
00:05:28.791 --> 00:05:30.540
But the date is wrong.

20
00:05:31.083 --> 00:05:32.790
It says he had no kids.

21
00:05:33.666 --> 00:05:34.666
Yes.

22
00:05:36.708 --> 00:05:38.832
- I'm his daughter.
- You're his daughter?

23
00:05:38.916 --> 00:05:40.184
Otherwise.
that paper is useless to me.

24
00:05:40.208 --> 00:05:42.915
The declarant is Alfonso Piñeiro.

25
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:44.249
Who's this man?

26
00:05:46.125 --> 00:05:47.290
Alfonso Piñeiro...

27
00:05:47.791 --> 00:05:49.374
I guess it's my granddad.

28
00:05:49.458 --> 00:05:51.249
- Your granddad?
- That's his name. yes.

29
00:05:52.416 --> 00:05:56.374
Well. at the time.
he said your dad had no kids.

30
00:06:01.125 --> 00:06:02.832
Is he alive?
- Yes.

31
00:06:02.916 --> 00:06:04.915
- And your grandmother?
- Yes.

32
00:06:05.583 --> 00:06:07.874
There's a way to fix it. then.

33
00:06:07.958 --> 00:06:10.165
Talk to your grandparents.

34
00:06:10.250 --> 00:06:13.457
have them sign a sworn declaration
before a notary.

35
00:06:14.291 --> 00:06:17.915
then the notary
will inform the civil registry

36
00:06:18.291 --> 00:06:22.374
and we'll put on the certificate
that you're his daughter.

37
00:06:26.583 --> 00:06:28.832
- My grandparents?
- Yes.

38
00:06:28.916 --> 00:06:32.165
Can't you just put an asterisk

39
00:06:32.250 --> 00:06:33.832
and put my name here?

40
00:07:08.166 --> 00:07:09.166
Marina?

41
00:07:10.291 --> 00:07:11.874
Marina Piñeiro.

42
00:07:18.083 --> 00:07:19.874
Welcome. At last!

43
00:07:19.958 --> 00:07:20.958
Thanks.

44
00:07:24.291 --> 00:07:26.165
Too many years have passed.

45
00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:31.124
Did you get the paper
for your grant?

46
00:07:31.208 --> 00:07:32.999
No. actually.
The paper's wrong.

47
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:36.249
We'll have to fix it.
I'll help however I can.

48
00:07:36.666 --> 00:07:38.749
Can I carry something?
- No. it's fine.

49
00:07:43.333 --> 00:07:45.165
They're cool. thanks.

50
00:07:46.250 --> 00:07:47.707
I've never had any of these.

51
00:07:47.791 --> 00:07:49.457
You'll use them plenty here.

52
00:07:51.208 --> 00:07:52.707
Feeling sick?

53
00:07:52.791 --> 00:07:54.415
- No. I'm fine for now.
- Yeah?

54
00:07:55.541 --> 00:07:57.165
I'm not wearing Nuno's.

55
00:07:57.250 --> 00:07:59.249
I can't go in otherwise.

56
00:08:00.333 --> 00:08:02.874
Can't you see it's size XL?

57
00:08:03.166 --> 00:08:05.290
It's XL. extra large

58
00:08:19.416 --> 00:08:21.665
Hey. hey. hey.
Eugène's getting mad.

59
00:08:22.416 --> 00:08:23.874
Nuno. Nuno. stop.

60
00:08:24.208 --> 00:08:25.624
Leave him alone.

61
00:08:26.625 --> 00:08:28.582
- Enough.
- They took my swimsuit.

62
00:08:28.666 --> 00:08:29.790
- Stop.
- It's fine.

63
00:08:29.875 --> 00:08:31.832
- I can't go swimming though.
- Swim naked.

64
00:08:31.916 --> 00:08:34.457
- I'm not swimming naked.
- Enough.

65
00:08:35.333 --> 00:08:38.165
Are the cousins you live with
just as annoying?

66
00:08:38.250 --> 00:08:41.582
They're my cousins.
but they're like my siblings.

67
00:08:43.083 --> 00:08:45.582
Lois is so happy to have you here.

68
00:08:46.416 --> 00:08:48.874
I mean.
having a cousin you don't know...

69
00:08:48.958 --> 00:08:50.082
it's weird. right?

70
00:08:52.958 --> 00:08:54.124
Let's take a photo...

71
00:08:57.458 --> 00:09:00.207
- You're just like your mum.
- Yes.

72
00:09:03.416 --> 00:09:05.290
Do your parents live in Vigo?

73
00:09:05.958 --> 00:09:09.040
On the outskirts.
We'll visit them in a couple of days.

74
00:09:10.541 --> 00:09:12.082
Those are the Cíes Islands.

75
00:09:31.708 --> 00:09:33.374
Come on. Nuno!

76
00:09:33.458 --> 00:09:34.957
Race you to the beach!

77
00:09:36.791 --> 00:09:37.957
Is it cold?

78
00:09:38.708 --> 00:09:40.374
Three. two. one...

79
00:09:44.750 --> 00:09:45.874
It's freezing!

80
00:09:45.958 --> 00:09:47.332
He who dares. Nuno.

81
00:09:48.291 --> 00:09:49.291
It's freezing. guys!

82
00:09:49.333 --> 00:09:51.040
What will your cousin think?

83
00:09:51.666 --> 00:09:53.249
You're too chicken to dive!

84
00:09:53.333 --> 00:09:56.999
If we didn't live in Madrid.
he'd be sailing every day.

85
00:09:59.708 --> 00:10:01.290
Aren't you going in. Marina?

86
00:10:01.375 --> 00:10:03.040
- Come on!
- You dive in too.

87
00:10:03.125 --> 00:10:04.874
It's good for the circulation!

88
00:10:05.791 --> 00:10:08.165
- Dive in. Marina!
- Be warned: it's cold.

89
00:10:08.250 --> 00:10:10.832
- Only at first. Just do it.
- Is it that cold?

90
00:10:10.916 --> 00:10:12.749
- Come on. Marina!
- Go on!

91
00:10:12.833 --> 00:10:14.457
Two...

92
00:10:14.541 --> 00:10:15.541
Three!

93
00:10:20.750 --> 00:10:23.249
- How is it?
- It's not the Mediterranean!

94
00:11:21.833 --> 00:11:23.249
Are they done?

95
00:11:23.708 --> 00:11:25.957
- Careful they don't burn.
- They won't.

96
00:11:26.791 --> 00:11:28.124
Add a Iittle salt.

97
00:11:29.041 --> 00:11:30.665
That one needs more salt.

98
00:11:30.750 --> 00:11:33.415
- Can I help?
- No. don't worry. love.

99
00:11:33.750 --> 00:11:35.082
Lois is an expert.

100
00:11:35.625 --> 00:11:37.249
Not exactly...

101
00:11:38.083 --> 00:11:39.832
- Do you like sardines?
- Yes.

102
00:11:39.833 --> 00:11:40.415
Yes.

103
00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:41.707
It smells good.

104
00:11:41.791 --> 00:11:43.415
I hope they taste as good.

105
00:11:44.958 --> 00:11:46.124
It's an experiment.

106
00:11:48.125 --> 00:11:49.624
My parents lived there. right?

107
00:11:49.708 --> 00:11:51.124
In that tall building.

108
00:11:51.583 --> 00:11:53.499
Toralla. I think.

109
00:11:53.583 --> 00:11:55.540
- You've been digging?
- Yeah.

110
00:11:56.083 --> 00:11:58.457
I read it in my mum's diary.

111
00:11:58.541 --> 00:12:00.749
They lived
in the building opposite...

112
00:12:00.833 --> 00:12:01.999
What are you doing?

113
00:12:04.208 --> 00:12:07.332
Honestly. he's like a four-year-old.
Look at him.

114
00:12:07.416 --> 00:12:08.416
Honestly...

115
00:12:08.958 --> 00:12:10.832
No. it can't have been Toralla.

116
00:12:10.916 --> 00:12:15.415
For a long time. your parents lived
in the building facing Samil beach.

117
00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:19.207
for two or three years
until your mum fell pregnant.

118
00:12:21.583 --> 00:12:23.999
No. my mum got pregnant in Barcelona.

119
00:12:24.416 --> 00:12:25.707
No. it was here.

120
00:12:25.791 --> 00:12:28.957
The idea was
to bring you up here. in Vigo.

121
00:12:29.625 --> 00:12:31.957
But your mum
wanted to go back to Barcelona.

122
00:12:32.041 --> 00:12:33.624
That's when they broke up.

123
00:12:35.375 --> 00:12:38.332
Didn't they break up
when Fon got sick?

124
00:12:38.875 --> 00:12:41.207
No. that was way before.

125
00:12:41.291 --> 00:12:42.457
It was before.

126
00:12:42.541 --> 00:12:45.082
- Is it ready?
- Get off. you'll burn yourself.

127
00:12:45.166 --> 00:12:46.499
Nuno. stop.

128
00:12:47.333 --> 00:12:48.749
- It's not ready.
- Here.

129
00:12:49.666 --> 00:12:50.749
Thanks. Mum.

130
00:12:51.666 --> 00:12:53.874
Her parents lived
on Samil beach. right?

131
00:12:53.958 --> 00:12:56.082
I don't know. we only went once.

132
00:12:56.166 --> 00:12:57.499
Maybe you only went once.

133
00:12:58.208 --> 00:13:00.124
I went a few times.

134
00:13:00.208 --> 00:13:02.499
And I know for a fact it was Samil.

135
00:13:03.833 --> 00:13:05.249
Kids. please.

136
00:13:09.208 --> 00:13:10.208
Yes.

137
00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:12.166
Yes. yes.

138
00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:13.290
Okay. I'm ready.

139
00:13:14.208 --> 00:13:15.665
Great. they're really nice.

140
00:13:15.750 --> 00:13:18.915
Yes. they get a bit mixed up.
but they're really nice.

141
00:13:20.250 --> 00:13:22.749
Nothing.
just with the things they tell me.

142
00:13:23.666 --> 00:13:24.582
No big deal.

143
00:13:24.666 --> 00:13:27.707
Mum. I'm on a really cool
sailing boat.

144
00:13:28.166 --> 00:13:31.290
I don't know what normal ones
are like. but it's really cool.

145
00:13:31.375 --> 00:13:35.749
It's much bigger
than it looks from the outside.

146
00:13:35.833 --> 00:13:37.915
It must be really expensive.

147
00:13:38.916 --> 00:13:40.415
Put her on. okay.

148
00:13:47.208 --> 00:13:48.415
Hi. Grandma!

149
00:13:50.208 --> 00:13:53.249
Great. here with the kids
cleaning forests.

150
00:13:57.291 --> 00:13:59.040
Of course they feed us.

151
00:14:04.250 --> 00:14:06.499
Yeah. there's one handsome boy.

152
00:14:06.583 --> 00:14:08.582
but I don't want a boyfriend.

153
00:14:09.791 --> 00:14:12.124
Yes. Grandma.
of course I'll come back.

154
00:14:13.208 --> 00:14:14.540
Yes. don't worry. I will.

155
00:14:21.125 --> 00:14:22.624
Not yet. but...

156
00:14:24.250 --> 00:14:27.082
Paperwork problems.
I'm sorting it out.

157
00:14:27.666 --> 00:14:28.999
I've talked to Lois.

158
00:14:32.708 --> 00:14:35.832
No. it's fine. he's helping me.

159
00:14:36.750 --> 00:14:38.540
Okay. speak soon.

160
00:14:38.625 --> 00:14:40.374
<i>Did you speak to your parents?</i>

161
00:14:40.458 --> 00:14:44.207
<i>Yes. they don't know.
they need to organise themselves.</i>

162
00:14:44.833 --> 00:14:47.415
<i>If they don't want us. we won't go.
They're missing out.</i>

163
00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:49.374
<i>- They're confused.
- What about your sister?</i>

164
00:14:50.083 --> 00:14:52.832
<i>All these arrangements...</i>

165
00:14:54.208 --> 00:14:57.665
<i>If she wants to meet them all.
I can't deny her that.</i>

166
00:14:58.250 --> 00:14:59.915
<i>Nuno. are you okay?</i>

167
00:15:02.666 --> 00:15:03.957
<i>You're struggling a bit.</i>

168
00:15:04.041 --> 00:15:05.249
<i>I just shuffled.</i>

169
00:15:06.875 --> 00:15:08.332
<i>Let me see.</i>

170
00:15:08.416 --> 00:15:10.624
He smoked a joint.
I can't believe it.

171
00:15:10.708 --> 00:15:13.415
- What did we say about this?
- Too far.

172
00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:14.790
Druggie.

173
00:15:14.875 --> 00:15:16.415
Go on. off you go.

174
00:15:16.500 --> 00:15:18.749
- Offyou go.
- I'm out of patience.

175
00:15:18.833 --> 00:15:21.124
What's this? A new jumper?

176
00:15:36.916 --> 00:15:39.415
<i>April 22nd. 1984.</i>

177
00:15:41.583 --> 00:15:43.749
<i>It's 7:30 p.m. and I'm with Fon.</i>

178
00:15:44.416 --> 00:15:45.582
<i>He's taking a nap.</i>

179
00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:48.790
<i>I love watching him sleep.</i>

180
00:15:49.458 --> 00:15:51.957
<i>You can see his dimples.</i>

181
00:15:53.916 --> 00:15:56.874
<i>When we arrived yesterday.
the tide was out.</i>

182
00:15:56.958 --> 00:16:00.165
<i>We caught crabs
and ate them for dinner.</i>

183
00:16:01.708 --> 00:16:03.207
<i>The Cíes are so beautiful.</i>

184
00:16:04.708 --> 00:16:07.749
<i>We're in a tent.
just like in the old days.</i>

185
00:16:08.958 --> 00:16:12.540
<i>Completely alone with just the sound
of the sea and the birds.</i>

186
00:16:41.666 --> 00:16:45.624
<i>Lord. our Father.
Hear our prayers</i>

187
00:16:45.708 --> 00:16:49.832
<i>and grant all those lost at sea...</i>

188
00:16:49.916 --> 00:16:52.457
<i>Give them eternal peace. Lord.</i>

189
00:16:54.541 --> 00:16:56.457
<i>From God's great mercy.</i>

190
00:16:56.541 --> 00:17:00.582
<i>saviour of souls lost at sea...</i>

191
00:17:33.708 --> 00:17:35.249
Look who's here.

192
00:17:35.333 --> 00:17:36.499
Hello!

193
00:17:36.583 --> 00:17:37.874
What are they doing here?

194
00:17:38.708 --> 00:17:40.415
Look how smart your grandma looks.

195
00:17:40.500 --> 00:17:41.500
Hello!

196
00:17:43.166 --> 00:17:44.290
Hello!

197
00:17:44.625 --> 00:17:45.457
Look. Marina.

198
00:17:45.541 --> 00:17:46.790
Our grandparents.

199
00:17:52.250 --> 00:17:54.790
I just don't get it.
I don't get it.

200
00:17:56.750 --> 00:17:57.915
Nuno. give me the helm.

201
00:17:58.000 --> 00:17:59.374
The family are there.
You go.

202
00:18:00.375 --> 00:18:03.124
Why are they here?
Didn't they say?

203
00:18:06.833 --> 00:18:07.833
Hello!

204
00:18:10.333 --> 00:18:12.749
Why are they doing here?
They weren't coming...

205
00:18:33.416 --> 00:18:35.874
What's it like
meeting Gran and Grandpa like that?

206
00:18:36.333 --> 00:18:37.540
Interesting.

207
00:18:37.625 --> 00:18:39.665
You're lucky you didn't grow up here.

208
00:19:08.291 --> 00:19:09.374
Hey.

209
00:19:13.375 --> 00:19:14.957
- Good night.
- Night.

210
00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:25.874
Day 2:
July 17. 2004

211
00:19:25.958 --> 00:19:28.707
Who would I be

212
00:19:28.791 --> 00:19:32.999
if my father's family
had raised me?

213
00:19:53.708 --> 00:19:55.124
Excuse me. Hi.

214
00:19:55.208 --> 00:19:56.832
- Hi.
- Do you live here?

215
00:19:56.916 --> 00:19:57.916
Yes.

216
00:19:58.666 --> 00:20:03.457
Can you see the Cíes Islands.
Cangas or Moaña from your windows?

217
00:20:03.541 --> 00:20:05.957
From the windows on this side. yes.

218
00:20:07.333 --> 00:20:10.374
Will you sing me the cat song?

219
00:20:10.458 --> 00:20:13.124
It's not a song. love. it's a poem.

220
00:20:13.625 --> 00:20:17.457
"Once I had a black and white cat
who was so beautiful

221
00:20:17.541 --> 00:20:20.332
with a thick tail
and he was called Serafín".

222
00:20:20.666 --> 00:20:23.915
Do you want some cold lemonade
or are you in a hurry?

223
00:20:24.250 --> 00:20:25.832
Okay. yes. one second.

224
00:20:25.916 --> 00:20:26.916
Thanks.

225
00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:29.040
Will you help me?

226
00:20:34.291 --> 00:20:36.957
How's it going?
Is it coming along well?

227
00:20:37.791 --> 00:20:39.499
- More or less.
- Okay.

228
00:20:40.375 --> 00:20:42.874
Your accent isn't familiar.
Where are you from?

229
00:20:42.958 --> 00:20:45.165
- You're not Galician?
- No. Catalan.

230
00:20:45.250 --> 00:20:47.249
Ah. you're Catalan.

231
00:20:47.791 --> 00:20:49.832
You don't remember a Piñeiro?

232
00:20:49.916 --> 00:20:51.874
No. because Piñeiro...

233
00:20:51.958 --> 00:20:54.582
- Mum. sit down.
- Let's sit down.

234
00:20:54.666 --> 00:20:57.040
It's to do with pine trees.
in Galicia...

235
00:20:57.125 --> 00:20:59.124
- Maybe...
- It's a common surname.

236
00:20:59.208 --> 00:21:00.499
Where are you off to. Iittle one?

237
00:21:01.166 --> 00:21:02.749
Maybe Fon...

238
00:21:03.916 --> 00:21:06.249
- Your dad was called...
- Well. Alfonso.

239
00:21:06.333 --> 00:21:07.790
Alfonso or Fon.

240
00:21:07.875 --> 00:21:10.457
No. it doesn't ring any bells.

241
00:21:10.958 --> 00:21:14.249
What year did they live here?

242
00:21:14.625 --> 00:21:16.999
It was...
I'm not really sure.

243
00:21:17.083 --> 00:21:18.582
It was before 1986.

244
00:21:18.666 --> 00:21:21.040
My dad died in 1987
when I was a baby.

245
00:21:21.125 --> 00:21:23.957
I came to live here in 1987.

246
00:21:24.041 --> 00:21:26.165
It was my second marriage and...

247
00:21:26.250 --> 00:21:29.249
Mum. Teresa lived here.
the neighbour upstairs.

248
00:21:29.333 --> 00:21:32.624
- We could ask her.
- Forget Teresa.

249
00:21:32.708 --> 00:21:35.332
I've told you several times now.

250
00:21:35.416 --> 00:21:37.582
Teresa's not well.
she has Alzheimer's.

251
00:21:38.166 --> 00:21:41.374
Teresa doesn't work.
she won't remember anything.

252
00:21:41.458 --> 00:21:44.082
Couldn't your mum tell you?

253
00:21:44.166 --> 00:21:47.457
My biological mother died
a few years later. so...

254
00:21:47.541 --> 00:21:50.457
Really? They both died?
In an accident or something?

255
00:21:50.541 --> 00:21:51.624
Mum...

256
00:21:51.708 --> 00:21:52.582
Well...

257
00:21:52.666 --> 00:21:56.040
I'm just asking the girl. because...

258
00:21:56.125 --> 00:21:57.374
It's her business.

259
00:22:32.333 --> 00:22:34.790
<i>November 28th. 1985.</i>

260
00:22:37.666 --> 00:22:39.832
<i>I've been working
in a comic shop for a while.</i>

261
00:22:40.875 --> 00:22:42.165
<i>It's so cool.</i>

262
00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:45.207
<i>I open at noon and work until 2 p.m.</i>

263
00:22:45.291 --> 00:22:47.207
<i>and then from 6 to 10 p.m.</i>

264
00:22:49.541 --> 00:22:51.665
<i>The street's full of wine
and rad bars.</i>

265
00:22:51.750 --> 00:22:53.374
<i>It's always buzzing.</i>

266
00:22:55.666 --> 00:22:58.040
<i>It belongs to Fon's cousin. Xulia.</i>

267
00:22:58.125 --> 00:22:59.457
<i>She's great.</i>

268
00:22:59.541 --> 00:23:00.999
<i>a real sweetheart.</i>

269
00:23:03.375 --> 00:23:05.499
<i>Unlike Fon's sisters.</i>

270
00:23:18.041 --> 00:23:21.040
- I liked the other one better.
- What's the problem with your arms?

271
00:23:21.125 --> 00:23:23.665
I don't want them on show.
I'd rather cover them.

272
00:23:23.750 --> 00:23:25.249
But Olalla...

273
00:23:25.333 --> 00:23:28.374
- It's just wedding jitters.
- It's genetics too.

274
00:23:29.291 --> 00:23:33.665
Why don't we put some natural silk
right down to your elbow?

275
00:23:34.416 --> 00:23:35.665
I'll try it.

276
00:23:35.750 --> 00:23:38.082
- I don't think so.
- Well I do!

277
00:23:38.166 --> 00:23:39.790
Who's getting married. you or me?

278
00:23:40.541 --> 00:23:42.749
And who's buying the dress?
You or me?

279
00:23:43.083 --> 00:23:45.957
How about I get Ángela
to measure you?

280
00:23:46.041 --> 00:23:47.582
You'll see how it feels.

281
00:23:47.666 --> 00:23:52.040
If you don't like it. don't worry.
there's loads of options.

282
00:23:52.125 --> 00:23:53.499
Thanks. Olalla.

283
00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:01.915
I'll be with you in a moment.

284
00:24:17.791 --> 00:24:20.582
Virginia. put my daughters
in the car and come here.

285
00:24:20.666 --> 00:24:23.165
Now. I won't argue.
Just come here.

286
00:24:23.250 --> 00:24:24.250
Now.

287
00:24:24.875 --> 00:24:27.582
It's just my brother messed up.
like always.

288
00:24:27.666 --> 00:24:29.499
He said you were coming earlier.

289
00:24:29.958 --> 00:24:33.374
Now my sister's out delivering orders
with my daughters.

290
00:24:34.958 --> 00:24:38.165
Pepe. you can't cut
that material like that.

291
00:24:38.250 --> 00:24:40.999
- It needs cutting inside out.
- Okay. as you say.

292
00:24:42.708 --> 00:24:45.040
I'm obviously late.
I can come back later.

293
00:24:45.125 --> 00:24:46.624
No. it's no problem.

294
00:24:46.708 --> 00:24:50.457
I'm just tired of being
the only organiser in the family.

295
00:24:51.041 --> 00:24:52.665
Did you see the client?

296
00:24:53.458 --> 00:24:56.457
She had some arms on her!

297
00:24:56.541 --> 00:24:58.290
Like a tambourine.

298
00:24:59.166 --> 00:25:02.915
They want me to work miracles
like Our Lady of Lourdes.

299
00:25:03.000 --> 00:25:06.040
She can cut them off
and clap with her feet.

300
00:25:06.125 --> 00:25:09.374
Consuelo. where did my sister
leave that red dress?

301
00:25:09.916 --> 00:25:11.040
Look.

302
00:25:11.125 --> 00:25:12.374
with this material

303
00:25:12.875 --> 00:25:16.249
your gran made a shirt for your dad
after his military service.

304
00:25:16.333 --> 00:25:17.915
but it's old-fashioned now.

305
00:25:19.333 --> 00:25:21.499
I thought it'd be nice
to turn it into a dress.

306
00:25:21.583 --> 00:25:22.915
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

307
00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:24.249
Put your hair up.

308
00:25:26.875 --> 00:25:27.999
Oh my God...

309
00:25:28.375 --> 00:25:31.207
Now. everything comes from China
these days and this is...

310
00:25:32.458 --> 00:25:35.874
Girls. we have to redo this zip.

311
00:25:36.958 --> 00:25:39.540
- Here. Olalla.
- No. I'll do it. Thanks.

312
00:25:40.166 --> 00:25:42.207
Great! I got it right.

313
00:25:42.291 --> 00:25:45.582
Because you have
the same constitution as your mother.

314
00:25:45.958 --> 00:25:47.040
The spitting image.

315
00:25:48.708 --> 00:25:49.957
Okay. arms up.

316
00:25:55.000 --> 00:25:57.749
Don't move.
I don't want to prick you.

317
00:26:01.666 --> 00:26:02.666
Well?

318
00:26:04.875 --> 00:26:06.124
Do you have a boyfriend?

319
00:26:06.666 --> 00:26:07.666
No.

320
00:26:08.625 --> 00:26:09.625
I see.

321
00:26:10.458 --> 00:26:12.374
Only because you don't want one.

322
00:26:13.916 --> 00:26:15.915
I'll make your wedding dress.

323
00:26:16.000 --> 00:26:17.749
I don't think I'll get married.

324
00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:20.457
How modern of you.

325
00:26:27.750 --> 00:26:29.957
Well done. Antía. you did it!

326
00:26:30.375 --> 00:26:31.375
I can't.

327
00:26:31.666 --> 00:26:32.707
Well done.

328
00:26:36.666 --> 00:26:41.790
<i>You can also say "Bloody Mary"
three times in front of the mirror.</i>

329
00:26:41.875 --> 00:26:44.999
<i>- so you don't need to write it.
- Bloody Mary isn't scary.</i>

330
00:26:45.708 --> 00:26:47.540
But the Santa Compaña is.

331
00:26:47.625 --> 00:26:50.040
- Why?
- Lots of people come and take you.

332
00:26:50.125 --> 00:26:53.457
Marina's not scared of ghosts.
Are you. Marina?

333
00:26:53.791 --> 00:26:54.707
No.

334
00:26:54.791 --> 00:26:58.040
Marina. have you seen
the Santa Compaña?

335
00:26:58.458 --> 00:26:59.458
No.

336
00:27:00.750 --> 00:27:03.082
That's lucky because...

337
00:27:03.166 --> 00:27:05.332
- What is it?
- It's creepy.

338
00:27:05.666 --> 00:27:08.082
They're spirits that can't die.

339
00:27:09.083 --> 00:27:11.582
Dead people that never die.

340
00:27:12.541 --> 00:27:13.624
What. girls?

341
00:27:13.708 --> 00:27:17.665
Sabela. always the same.

342
00:27:17.750 --> 00:27:19.707
- You tell her.
- I'm not asking her.

343
00:27:19.791 --> 00:27:21.040
It was your idea.

344
00:27:21.125 --> 00:27:22.415
- You say it.
- Nothing.

345
00:27:22.500 --> 00:27:23.957
One question.

346
00:27:24.041 --> 00:27:26.124
Are you sick?
You don't look it.

347
00:27:27.708 --> 00:27:29.540
Sick? Why?

348
00:27:29.625 --> 00:27:32.124
Our mum said
that we can't touch your blood.

349
00:27:32.208 --> 00:27:34.207
That we can't touch you.

350
00:27:35.458 --> 00:27:37.332
What happened when you were a baby?

351
00:27:37.416 --> 00:27:40.332
- You took ages. Auntie.
- You did.

352
00:27:42.875 --> 00:27:45.249
- Did my sister give that to you?
- Yes.

353
00:27:45.625 --> 00:27:46.707
Great.

354
00:27:46.791 --> 00:27:48.999
Genius.
It was my idea.

355
00:27:49.583 --> 00:27:52.082
- Do you like it?
- Yes. I love it.

356
00:27:52.166 --> 00:27:53.999
I didn't know it was your idea.

357
00:27:54.416 --> 00:27:58.040
- Belts on. girls.
- Auntie. I need a wee.

358
00:27:58.791 --> 00:27:59.791
Seatbelt. Antía.

359
00:27:59.833 --> 00:28:01.915
I'll give you a bottle. if you want.

360
00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:02.915
Let's go.

361
00:28:03.000 --> 00:28:04.000
Okay. I'll piss in it.

362
00:28:04.041 --> 00:28:05.832
I can't believe
she gave it to you already.

363
00:28:25.291 --> 00:28:26.332
Oh my God.

364
00:28:27.125 --> 00:28:29.249
People in Vigo are
such gossips. Marina.

365
00:28:30.750 --> 00:28:33.290
They asked how my divorce is going.

366
00:28:33.375 --> 00:28:35.582
Don't you think that's rude?

367
00:28:36.458 --> 00:28:37.499
They don't care.

368
00:28:39.666 --> 00:28:42.207
Be careful. your mum will kill me!

369
00:28:45.958 --> 00:28:47.415
Where's Quique?

370
00:28:52.583 --> 00:28:54.457
I would've loved to bring you up.

371
00:28:55.041 --> 00:28:57.207
Quique would be a good brother.

372
00:28:57.291 --> 00:28:58.499
Sure.

373
00:29:00.416 --> 00:29:03.457
To be honest. it's a good job
my siblings didn't bring you up.

374
00:29:04.041 --> 00:29:06.374
One can't pay his own rent.

375
00:29:06.458 --> 00:29:09.499
The other
sucks up to clients all day.

376
00:29:09.583 --> 00:29:12.415
The third only comes
when he needs something.

377
00:29:12.500 --> 00:29:14.707
I'm the only normal one
in this family.

378
00:29:14.791 --> 00:29:16.082
How about that?

379
00:29:18.625 --> 00:29:20.999
I always told them to call you.
Marina.

380
00:29:21.083 --> 00:29:24.707
But your adoptive mum
wanted nothing to do with us.

381
00:29:24.791 --> 00:29:25.707
Right.

382
00:29:25.791 --> 00:29:29.165
Gran tried several times.
But she never got an answer.

383
00:29:30.875 --> 00:29:32.665
Your dad took it really hard.

384
00:30:11.750 --> 00:30:14.624
Good. I met my dad's sisters today.

385
00:30:14.708 --> 00:30:15.957
It went fine.

386
00:30:16.833 --> 00:30:17.833
They're peculiar.

387
00:30:20.625 --> 00:30:21.625
Mum.

388
00:30:25.208 --> 00:30:26.665
Is it possible that...

389
00:30:28.083 --> 00:30:31.249
Over the years.
maybe when I was Iittle...

390
00:30:33.166 --> 00:30:36.665
did Fon's mum call the house?

391
00:30:37.416 --> 00:30:38.624
Do you remember?

392
00:30:44.500 --> 00:30:46.749
Mum. they haven't said anything.

393
00:30:47.291 --> 00:30:48.291
No.

394
00:30:49.625 --> 00:30:53.749
That's not why I asked.
It was just a question.

395
00:30:54.166 --> 00:30:55.665
Sorry. it doesn't matter.

396
00:30:55.750 --> 00:30:57.332
I don't want to argue.

397
00:30:58.041 --> 00:30:59.041
Yes.

398
00:31:04.416 --> 00:31:06.124
No. not yet.

399
00:31:07.166 --> 00:31:11.499
No. I talked to Lois.
we'll do it with my grandparents.

400
00:31:13.333 --> 00:31:15.290
Don't worry. I'll get it.

401
00:31:16.791 --> 00:31:19.332
I'm coming home with the certificate.

402
00:31:19.416 --> 00:31:20.582
Don't worry.

403
00:31:23.166 --> 00:31:26.249
Day 3:
July 18. 2004

404
00:31:26.333 --> 00:31:33.165
How many ways
could you be young in the 80s?

405
00:31:54.500 --> 00:31:55.790
How's it going. Iittle niece?

406
00:31:57.291 --> 00:31:58.707
Isn't it a beautiful day?

407
00:31:59.250 --> 00:32:01.790
- I'm not sure.
- Yes. it's beautiful.

408
00:32:04.916 --> 00:32:06.756
This sea smells different
to the Mediterranean.

409
00:32:06.833 --> 00:32:08.040
Of course it does.

410
00:32:08.375 --> 00:32:09.957
This isn't a pond.

411
00:32:14.083 --> 00:32:17.040
My parents lived over there. right?

412
00:32:17.416 --> 00:32:18.874
- Where?
- In Samil.

413
00:32:18.958 --> 00:32:20.374
No. who told you that?

414
00:32:20.458 --> 00:32:21.458
Lois.

415
00:32:22.500 --> 00:32:23.332
They didn't?

416
00:32:23.416 --> 00:32:26.040
No. and Lois wouldn't know.
he was in France.

417
00:32:26.125 --> 00:32:29.499
They lived in the big building
next to that one.

418
00:32:29.583 --> 00:32:31.290
- In Toralla?
- Toralla. yes.

419
00:32:32.500 --> 00:32:34.124
That's what I thought.

420
00:32:34.625 --> 00:32:36.207
It was a cool time.

421
00:32:38.083 --> 00:32:40.290
Then they ran out of money. but...

422
00:32:42.000 --> 00:32:43.124
But it was cool.

423
00:32:47.333 --> 00:32:49.624
- Know why I brought you here?
- No.

424
00:32:49.708 --> 00:32:52.207
Your grandpa built this shipyard.

425
00:32:52.291 --> 00:32:53.499
- Really?
- Yes.

426
00:32:53.833 --> 00:32:54.749
It's his?

427
00:32:54.833 --> 00:32:57.499
No. none of us
wanted to work with him.

428
00:32:57.583 --> 00:32:58.957
It would've been hell.

429
00:32:59.041 --> 00:33:01.040
Have you met him yet?
- No.

430
00:33:01.125 --> 00:33:02.249
You will.

431
00:33:02.833 --> 00:33:04.040
But...

432
00:33:04.458 --> 00:33:05.540
"Piñeiro."

433
00:33:06.250 --> 00:33:07.250
There you have it.

434
00:33:07.291 --> 00:33:09.582
He sold it in the end.

435
00:33:11.291 --> 00:33:12.124
Hello.

436
00:33:12.208 --> 00:33:13.249
Can we go up?

437
00:33:14.791 --> 00:33:15.791
I don't know.

438
00:33:18.916 --> 00:33:20.790
I don't know whether to believe him.

439
00:33:20.875 --> 00:33:22.957
but your grandpa told me

440
00:33:23.041 --> 00:33:27.290
that barnacles got stuck to the boats
and they cleaned them here.

441
00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:30.457
If not. they couldn't move.

442
00:33:31.083 --> 00:33:34.165
- Why not?
- The barnacles slowed them down.

443
00:33:34.833 --> 00:33:36.207
They had to clean them.

444
00:33:36.541 --> 00:33:39.957
I don't know if it's true.
your grandpa exaggerates.

445
00:33:40.041 --> 00:33:41.041
Hello.

446
00:33:43.791 --> 00:33:44.832
Isn't it cool?

447
00:33:46.583 --> 00:33:47.915
Look over there.

448
00:34:00.125 --> 00:34:01.540
Your dad slept there.

449
00:34:11.416 --> 00:34:13.040
This is my favourite place.

450
00:34:15.625 --> 00:34:16.874
Shit!

451
00:34:16.958 --> 00:34:18.624
Look. look!
Did you see it?

452
00:34:18.708 --> 00:34:21.082
- Yes.
- It comes sometimes.

453
00:34:21.166 --> 00:34:24.165
- You know it?
- Yes. It's a clever cat.

454
00:34:25.166 --> 00:34:26.290
Isn't it hot?

455
00:34:27.583 --> 00:34:28.583
Yes.

456
00:34:46.500 --> 00:34:47.540
It doesn't work.

457
00:34:48.625 --> 00:34:49.790
Yes. keep going.

458
00:34:58.041 --> 00:34:59.665
Let's go outside.

459
00:35:05.916 --> 00:35:08.915
This place is full of memories.

460
00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:13.874
I remember your dad sailing
with flamenco music blasting out.

461
00:35:13.958 --> 00:35:14.999
- Flamenco?
- Yes.

462
00:35:15.083 --> 00:35:17.207
He started sailing because of me.
- Really?

463
00:35:17.291 --> 00:35:20.290
Yes. He came to a regatta
with some friends.

464
00:35:21.166 --> 00:35:22.915
That's the sea for you.

465
00:35:23.000 --> 00:35:25.207
You like it. you're hooked.

466
00:35:25.291 --> 00:35:26.124
Right.

467
00:35:26.208 --> 00:35:27.957
Your dad sailed until his final days.

468
00:35:29.208 --> 00:35:31.832
He thought AIDS was made up.

469
00:35:31.916 --> 00:35:33.082
Anyway...

470
00:35:33.166 --> 00:35:34.540
He went everywhere.

471
00:35:34.625 --> 00:35:37.207
crossed the Atlantic.
- In this boat?

472
00:35:37.291 --> 00:35:39.582
Yes. To Peru. with your mum.

473
00:35:39.666 --> 00:35:41.999
- I read that in her diary.
- Really?

474
00:35:42.375 --> 00:35:43.582
In her diary?

475
00:35:44.333 --> 00:35:47.790
But never to Barcelona to see you.
I always told him to go.

476
00:35:49.791 --> 00:35:51.874
He didn't have much time.

477
00:35:51.958 --> 00:35:53.832
- Right.
- I was very Iittle.

478
00:35:54.583 --> 00:35:57.332
There are so many stories
on this boat.

479
00:35:58.041 --> 00:36:00.124
Plus those I don't know about.

480
00:36:01.166 --> 00:36:03.040
I remember once...

481
00:36:03.833 --> 00:36:05.665
The mast was struck by lightning.

482
00:36:05.750 --> 00:36:09.540
they were loaded up on H
off the coast of Portugal.

483
00:36:09.625 --> 00:36:14.040
A huge mess. the cops caught them.
They were unlucky.

484
00:36:14.125 --> 00:36:16.290
We had to drive down
to pick them up...

485
00:36:17.125 --> 00:36:18.290
H?

486
00:36:19.083 --> 00:36:21.374
- What's H?
- You know. horse.

487
00:36:21.833 --> 00:36:22.874
Heroin.

488
00:36:27.041 --> 00:36:29.415
I didn't know they sold it too.

489
00:36:29.500 --> 00:36:30.582
Was it for...?

490
00:36:31.625 --> 00:36:32.749
What didn't they do?

491
00:36:34.041 --> 00:36:35.457
What didn't they do?

492
00:37:32.458 --> 00:37:34.999
<i>November 17th. 1983.</i>

493
00:37:36.458 --> 00:37:39.082
<i>Friday afternoon.
Fon fought with his brother</i>

494
00:37:39.166 --> 00:37:40.707
<i>and didn't go to work today.</i>

495
00:37:41.958 --> 00:37:43.624
<i>We have a thousand ideas.</i>

496
00:37:43.708 --> 00:37:46.582
<i>If he quits.
there's nothing for us in Vigo.</i>

497
00:37:48.208 --> 00:37:50.457
<i>There's a regatta.
England to Bayonne.</i>

498
00:37:50.541 --> 00:37:52.832
<i>Fon wants to enter his boat.</i>

499
00:37:54.250 --> 00:37:57.957
<i>I want to go and sell clothes
and other things I buy in London.</i>

500
00:38:00.750 --> 00:38:02.290
<i>We also want to go to Peru.</i>

501
00:38:04.625 --> 00:38:06.124
<i>We have so many plans.</i>

502
00:38:15.708 --> 00:38:18.874
<i>I'll do it how I want.
but she's leaving with that document.</i>

503
00:38:19.458 --> 00:38:22.957
<i>That's it.
I'll find a way to do it.</i>

504
00:38:24.166 --> 00:38:26.249
Let's see what happens
with my parents.

505
00:38:29.708 --> 00:38:31.207
She Iooksjust like her mum.

506
00:38:43.166 --> 00:38:44.790
- Who wants a beer?
- Me.

507
00:38:44.875 --> 00:38:46.040
Me too.

508
00:38:46.541 --> 00:38:47.624
Thank you.

509
00:38:50.875 --> 00:38:52.415
Want a beer. Marina?

510
00:38:52.500 --> 00:38:53.582
I don't drink.

511
00:38:54.041 --> 00:38:55.832
The other Iittle orphan's
a goody-goody!

512
00:38:55.916 --> 00:38:57.332
What are you doing?

513
00:38:59.333 --> 00:39:01.040
You're a nosy parker.

514
00:39:01.125 --> 00:39:04.290
- You're looking for something.
- Funny.

515
00:39:04.375 --> 00:39:05.957
What are you looking for?

516
00:39:06.041 --> 00:39:07.374
Let her look!

517
00:39:07.791 --> 00:39:08.832
Same as always.

518
00:39:09.625 --> 00:39:11.540
Hurry up. we're hungry.

519
00:39:12.583 --> 00:39:14.582
- That's the main thing.
- Bingo!

520
00:39:14.666 --> 00:39:16.457
You've made yourself at home.

521
00:39:16.541 --> 00:39:17.707
I mean...

522
00:39:18.041 --> 00:39:20.290
She's here more
than at her own house.

523
00:39:20.375 --> 00:39:21.832
She has loads. she won't notice.

524
00:39:21.916 --> 00:39:22.790
- True.
- Okay.

525
00:39:22.875 --> 00:39:24.707
You finally learned
how to roll joints?

526
00:39:24.791 --> 00:39:25.791
Did you?

527
00:39:27.500 --> 00:39:29.249
- Save something for me.
- Shut up.

528
00:39:29.333 --> 00:39:32.374
- None of this either. Marina?
- No.

529
00:39:32.458 --> 00:39:36.165
Smoking a joint won't turn us
into our parents. you know.

530
00:39:37.250 --> 00:39:38.250
Of course.

531
00:39:43.041 --> 00:39:44.124
Look.

532
00:39:44.208 --> 00:39:45.707
Who's that with the flowing locks?

533
00:39:46.041 --> 00:39:47.249
Flowing locks...

534
00:39:47.625 --> 00:39:48.749
It's Fon. isn't it?

535
00:39:48.833 --> 00:39:50.374
- And her?
- My mum.

536
00:39:50.458 --> 00:39:52.457
Look at her modern clothes.

537
00:39:53.750 --> 00:39:55.624
We spent a lot of time together.

538
00:39:56.625 --> 00:39:57.625
Where? Here?

539
00:39:57.708 --> 00:40:01.040
Yes. she stayed here for ages.

540
00:40:01.125 --> 00:40:03.124
Because my cousin was a badass.

541
00:40:04.083 --> 00:40:05.165
In what way?

542
00:40:05.250 --> 00:40:07.832
Well.
they sometimes ran out of money...

543
00:40:07.916 --> 00:40:10.249
- This is Cíes.
- ...your dad used to go...

544
00:40:11.458 --> 00:40:15.374
to your grandparents' house
and leave your mum stranded.

545
00:40:15.458 --> 00:40:18.957
I used to take her in
and that made us closer.

546
00:40:19.291 --> 00:40:20.291
<i>- Wow.</i>
- Yes.

547
00:40:20.333 --> 00:40:21.333
I didn't know.

548
00:40:22.041 --> 00:40:23.957
And my uncle...

549
00:40:24.041 --> 00:40:26.582
- What?
- Your dad was a bastard.

550
00:40:26.666 --> 00:40:28.415
- My dad?
- Yes. he was.

551
00:40:28.500 --> 00:40:32.290
He used to give your mum 5.000 pesetas
never to see your dad again.

552
00:40:32.833 --> 00:40:33.874
Seriously?

553
00:40:33.958 --> 00:40:35.124
That was your grandpa.

554
00:40:35.208 --> 00:40:37.040
- Grandpa?
- Well. he still is.

555
00:40:37.458 --> 00:40:39.207
Yes. but he didn't manage it.

556
00:40:39.291 --> 00:40:41.832
They loved each other.
despite their quarrels.

557
00:40:41.916 --> 00:40:42.916
You know.

558
00:40:43.000 --> 00:40:44.915
love and drugs isn't a good match...

559
00:40:45.000 --> 00:40:46.874
but they did love each other.

560
00:40:46.958 --> 00:40:49.332
Your mum was over the moon
about being pregnant.

561
00:40:49.708 --> 00:40:52.040
Look. I wanted to show you
this photo.

562
00:40:59.416 --> 00:41:01.165
This was a Iovely day.

563
00:41:01.666 --> 00:41:03.457
It's your parents

564
00:41:03.541 --> 00:41:07.415
with Lúa and Milton.
Uxia's parents.

565
00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:09.790
- They were friends?
- Yes. yes.

566
00:41:09.875 --> 00:41:11.165
Good friends.

567
00:41:11.708 --> 00:41:12.957
They lived next door.

568
00:41:13.291 --> 00:41:15.040
Look how pretty they were.

569
00:41:15.125 --> 00:41:17.665
Both pregnant at the same time.
all day together.

570
00:41:17.750 --> 00:41:19.957
They used to go out sailing.

571
00:41:20.041 --> 00:41:21.249
This one here.

572
00:41:21.625 --> 00:41:23.707
- that's your uncle Iago.
- Really?

573
00:41:23.791 --> 00:41:25.082
Let me see...

574
00:41:26.458 --> 00:41:29.249
- Do you remember?
- Of course I do.

575
00:41:30.208 --> 00:41:32.457
I'm the only one still alive.

576
00:41:32.541 --> 00:41:33.665
It's hard to believe.

577
00:41:35.291 --> 00:41:37.249
It was a massacre. at the time.

578
00:41:37.333 --> 00:41:39.499
They all dropped like flies.

579
00:41:40.333 --> 00:41:42.790
Accidents. overdoses or AIDS.

580
00:41:42.875 --> 00:41:46.415
We have other friends.
but it's not the same. right Iago?

581
00:41:46.500 --> 00:41:47.832
No. it's not the same.

582
00:41:48.708 --> 00:41:49.832
It's not the same.

583
00:41:59.166 --> 00:42:02.457
When your dad died in 1992.

584
00:42:03.500 --> 00:42:06.082
we lost two cousins too...

585
00:42:06.166 --> 00:42:08.957
My dad died in 1987.
not 1992. when I was a baby.

586
00:42:10.208 --> 00:42:11.582
No. Marina.

587
00:42:11.666 --> 00:42:14.290
He didn't die in 1987.
Who told you that?

588
00:42:16.666 --> 00:42:18.249
My family always said that.

589
00:42:19.958 --> 00:42:22.124
No. Marina. your dad died in 1992.

590
00:42:25.791 --> 00:42:28.082
But I would remember him.

591
00:42:28.750 --> 00:42:31.790
I was five. In five years
he couldn't come to Barcelona?

592
00:42:32.250 --> 00:42:34.665
No. he wasn't fit for that.

593
00:42:34.750 --> 00:42:38.707
Do you know what happened to him
when he felt ill?

594
00:42:38.791 --> 00:42:40.457
Well. when he got ill.

595
00:42:41.458 --> 00:42:44.082
He heard your mother's voice.
He said:

596
00:42:44.666 --> 00:42:47.207
"Bring Marina.
she's in the sitting room".

597
00:42:47.291 --> 00:42:49.499
I told him there was nobody there.

598
00:42:50.166 --> 00:42:53.874
He would insist:
"Marina's behind the door".

599
00:42:54.500 --> 00:42:56.374
But I wasn't there.

600
00:42:56.458 --> 00:42:58.874
No. but he heard your mum's voice

601
00:42:58.958 --> 00:43:00.999
and thought you were both here.

602
00:43:01.500 --> 00:43:03.374
I told him nobody was there.

603
00:43:03.458 --> 00:43:05.915
He said: "Open the door.
listen to me. Xu".

604
00:43:06.000 --> 00:43:07.415
He always called me "Xu".

605
00:46:11.875 --> 00:46:14.040
<i>March 10th. 1985.</i>

606
00:46:15.500 --> 00:46:16.665
<i>It's 4:30 p.m.</i>

607
00:46:16.750 --> 00:46:19.540
<i>and it's been ages since I slept.</i>

608
00:46:20.000 --> 00:46:21.290
<i>And I'm wasted.</i>

609
00:46:22.666 --> 00:46:26.790
<i>And my body's a wreck
from a bad trip last week.</i>

610
00:46:27.958 --> 00:46:29.999
<i>And now I'm listening to
Lole y Manuel.</i>

611
00:46:31.208 --> 00:46:34.207
<i>"And your eyes dig into me
Like a sword"</i>

612
00:46:35.125 --> 00:46:37.374
<i>Dig into me like a sword</i>

613
00:46:39.291 --> 00:46:42.124
<i>"Dig into me like a sword"</i>

614
00:46:49.250 --> 00:46:50.707
NOVEMBER 28. 1985

615
00:46:53.208 --> 00:46:55.582
FEBRUARY 23. 1986

616
00:46:57.208 --> 00:46:59.374
FEBRUARY 24. 1986

617
00:47:07.333 --> 00:47:08.832
MARCH 3. 1986

618
00:48:04.333 --> 00:48:07.207
Day 4:
July 19. 2004

619
00:48:07.291 --> 00:48:14.374
Does sharing the same blood
make you part of the same family?

620
00:48:22.875 --> 00:48:24.624
MUM CALLING

621
00:48:42.291 --> 00:48:43.582
<i>We're late.</i>

622
00:48:43.666 --> 00:48:45.124
<i>Come on. let's go.</i>

623
00:48:58.000 --> 00:48:59.915
<i>Where is your cousin?</i>

624
00:49:01.625 --> 00:49:03.790
<i>The bride wore something old.
something new.</i>

625
00:49:03.875 --> 00:49:06.082
<i>something borrowed.
and something blue.</i>

626
00:49:06.166 --> 00:49:08.749
<i>The old represents her past.</i>

627
00:49:08.833 --> 00:49:10.374
<i>in this case. a beautiful fan...</i>

628
00:49:12.541 --> 00:49:13.541
Mum?

629
00:49:18.166 --> 00:49:19.540
Mum. we're all here.

630
00:49:19.625 --> 00:49:21.707
- Hi. son.
- Marina's here too.

631
00:49:33.708 --> 00:49:34.708
Mum...

632
00:49:35.666 --> 00:49:38.915
Did you see the rain that day?
What bad luck.

633
00:49:39.000 --> 00:49:40.000
Yes. yes.

634
00:49:40.500 --> 00:49:43.665
Victoria told me.
she was invited to the wedding.

635
00:49:43.750 --> 00:49:45.332
I don't know why.

636
00:49:47.166 --> 00:49:50.915
The dress was filthy.
the train covered in mud.

637
00:49:51.500 --> 00:49:52.624
Look. Mum.

638
00:49:53.291 --> 00:49:54.457
This is Marina.

639
00:49:55.916 --> 00:49:56.916
Hi.

640
00:49:59.625 --> 00:50:02.499
Why's it taken you so long
to come and see us?

641
00:50:03.000 --> 00:50:04.499
What do you mean. Mum?

642
00:50:05.750 --> 00:50:08.874
She just turned 18.
she couldn't travel alone before.

643
00:50:08.958 --> 00:50:11.040
You don't look like your mum.

644
00:50:13.666 --> 00:50:16.624
- Granny...
- Gran. can we swim in the pool?

645
00:50:16.708 --> 00:50:17.708
Hey. say hello first.

646
00:50:17.750 --> 00:50:20.707
Hey. I'll infect you
with whatever I've got.

647
00:50:20.791 --> 00:50:22.582
Headaches aren't contagious. Mum.

648
00:50:22.666 --> 00:50:24.665
- Can we swim?
- No. you can't.

649
00:50:24.750 --> 00:50:25.790
Why?

650
00:50:25.875 --> 00:50:29.582
Because the water's clean.
I don't want you getting it dirty.

651
00:50:30.041 --> 00:50:33.374
No. go on. get out.
You're crowding me.

652
00:50:33.458 --> 00:50:35.624
Why have a pool. then?

653
00:50:35.958 --> 00:50:37.915
- Well...
- Maybe later.

654
00:50:38.000 --> 00:50:39.165
Let's go. Antía.

655
00:50:41.625 --> 00:50:42.625
Come on.

656
00:50:43.083 --> 00:50:44.790
Are you okay?
Let's go.

657
00:50:46.416 --> 00:50:49.124
Come on. Mum.
It's time for your tablet.

658
00:50:49.208 --> 00:50:51.582
You're so annoying with that tablet.

659
00:50:52.208 --> 00:50:54.457
I don't want a tablet.

660
00:50:55.583 --> 00:50:57.415
You don't know what's wrong with me.

661
00:50:57.500 --> 00:50:58.665
What is wrong with you?

662
00:50:58.750 --> 00:51:01.749
I'm in no state
for all this hustle and bustle.

663
00:51:02.500 --> 00:51:04.082
What a Iovely thought. Mum.

664
00:51:04.166 --> 00:51:06.999
I've been trying to decide
between cremation or burial.

665
00:51:07.083 --> 00:51:10.040
- How nice!
- The church allows cremation now.

666
00:51:10.458 --> 00:51:11.499
Fantastic.

667
00:51:13.541 --> 00:51:15.874
I'm not taking any tablets.

668
00:51:15.958 --> 00:51:18.915
She's impossible with those tablets.

669
00:51:19.000 --> 00:51:21.249
You're so patient. Consuelo.

670
00:51:21.333 --> 00:51:22.457
I'm just going to die.

671
00:51:22.541 --> 00:51:25.374
I went to the hairdresser
for my last colour.

672
00:51:25.458 --> 00:51:27.249
manicure and pedicure.

673
00:51:27.333 --> 00:51:28.499
So I'm ready.

674
00:51:29.583 --> 00:51:30.957
- She's just...
- Let her.

675
00:51:31.041 --> 00:51:32.041
Antía.

676
00:51:32.500 --> 00:51:33.749
Antía. no.

677
00:51:33.833 --> 00:51:36.374
- Gran will love that.
- Look. it's "graffito".

678
00:51:37.833 --> 00:51:38.874
She will kill you.

679
00:51:42.333 --> 00:51:44.665
There's your cousin.

680
00:51:45.625 --> 00:51:46.665
Antía!

681
00:51:47.458 --> 00:51:49.290
Damn it!

682
00:51:49.833 --> 00:51:52.290
No. don't laugh. bad girl!

683
00:51:52.375 --> 00:51:54.082
You can't do that. bad girl!

684
00:51:54.166 --> 00:51:56.707
No. it's not funny!

685
00:51:56.791 --> 00:51:58.790
- What are you doing?
- Antía!

686
00:51:58.875 --> 00:52:00.915
Don't talk to her like that.

687
00:52:04.041 --> 00:52:06.332
Who gave Antía the lipstick?

688
00:52:06.416 --> 00:52:08.165
- It was there.
- It was on the table.

689
00:52:09.333 --> 00:52:10.333
Well?

690
00:52:10.791 --> 00:52:12.374
Shall I cut the ham myself?

691
00:52:12.458 --> 00:52:13.624
We're talking.

692
00:52:13.708 --> 00:52:16.082
- The rest of us are working.
- We're coming.

693
00:52:23.458 --> 00:52:25.707
She was at the civil registry

694
00:52:25.791 --> 00:52:28.207
and apparently
she couldn't get what she needed.

695
00:52:32.541 --> 00:52:33.790
Grandma's here.

696
00:52:37.291 --> 00:52:38.582
Thanks. Consuelo.

697
00:52:48.375 --> 00:52:50.624
Isn't it easier this way?

698
00:52:50.708 --> 00:52:53.249
No. it's harder that way.

699
00:52:53.791 --> 00:52:55.624
It's harder that way.

700
00:52:55.708 --> 00:52:58.707
- Where's the pie?
- The pie is over there.

701
00:52:59.416 --> 00:53:00.207
Great.

702
00:53:00.291 --> 00:53:03.457
She's just like her mother.
The spitting image.

703
00:53:03.541 --> 00:53:05.957
Mum. they didn't have
<i>the tocinillos.</i>

704
00:53:06.041 --> 00:53:08.540
I had to buy an assortment of cakes.

705
00:53:09.791 --> 00:53:11.624
- They're getting worse.
- They are.

706
00:53:11.708 --> 00:53:14.374
- Cuca reported them.
- Doesn't surprise me.

707
00:53:15.500 --> 00:53:16.500
So?

708
00:53:17.083 --> 00:53:18.499
Did Grandma like the dress?

709
00:53:18.833 --> 00:53:20.124
She didn't comment.

710
00:53:23.583 --> 00:53:25.124
- Mum?
- What?

711
00:53:25.208 --> 00:53:27.582
- Did you take your vitamins?
- Yes.

712
00:53:27.666 --> 00:53:29.707
- And the tablet for your sugar?
- Yes.

713
00:53:32.583 --> 00:53:35.249
Alfonso.
what are you doing with that?

714
00:53:36.041 --> 00:53:40.540
Showing it to my son and grandkids
if I'm allowed.

715
00:53:40.916 --> 00:53:42.624
- He's not answering.
- You're allowed.

716
00:53:42.708 --> 00:53:43.790
Iago's not coming.

717
00:53:45.791 --> 00:53:48.499
I was optimistic
thinking we could all make it.

718
00:53:48.583 --> 00:53:50.832
Your brother thinks this is a hotel.

719
00:53:50.916 --> 00:53:53.832
- Just this once.
- Iago's not coming?

720
00:53:54.541 --> 00:53:55.624
Doesn't look like it.

721
00:53:55.708 --> 00:53:57.832
What did you expect?
It's the festivities.

722
00:53:57.916 --> 00:53:59.999
- What is it?
- Uncle Pepito's walking stick.

723
00:54:00.083 --> 00:54:02.582
- Guys. look.
- What's that?

724
00:54:02.666 --> 00:54:05.040
- Uncle Pepito's walking stick.
- Look at the details.

725
00:54:05.125 --> 00:54:08.165
Very nice...
I'll put it back.

726
00:54:08.250 --> 00:54:10.332
They all have the same ring.

727
00:54:10.416 --> 00:54:12.290
Look out. it's going.

728
00:54:12.375 --> 00:54:13.375
It's going.

729
00:54:13.458 --> 00:54:15.790
You all cause such a fuss.

730
00:54:16.666 --> 00:54:20.374
Behave yourselves. you two.
I want a peaceful party.

731
00:54:20.458 --> 00:54:22.832
- What do you mean?
- I haven't told him yet.

732
00:54:23.500 --> 00:54:24.832
Told me what?

733
00:54:25.291 --> 00:54:26.415
Huh?

734
00:54:26.500 --> 00:54:27.500
Well...

735
00:54:29.708 --> 00:54:33.124
I need the boat this weekend.
you need to go to a hotel.

736
00:54:33.208 --> 00:54:34.290
Ah. okay...

737
00:54:34.375 --> 00:54:36.957
I'll clean it. air it
and fill the fridge with champagne.

738
00:54:37.041 --> 00:54:38.999
Lois. enough.

739
00:54:39.083 --> 00:54:42.124
- She did it again.
- We'll sort it out.

740
00:54:42.208 --> 00:54:43.957
- Why speak in French?
- I'll translate.

741
00:54:44.041 --> 00:54:47.665
I'm saying that we have to go
to a fucking hotel in my own city!

742
00:54:48.416 --> 00:54:50.707
Mum. everything's so expensive.

743
00:54:51.041 --> 00:54:53.832
There must be
bigger houses in Madrid.

744
00:54:53.916 --> 00:54:55.040
I keep saying that.

745
00:54:55.125 --> 00:54:57.499
Did you share with your brother?

746
00:54:58.041 --> 00:55:00.374
I did at boarding school.
It was fun.

747
00:55:00.458 --> 00:55:03.374
- If he has to change schools...
- What's the problem?

748
00:55:03.458 --> 00:55:07.124
- Let's hope Nuno passes.
- It's my fault now?

749
00:55:07.583 --> 00:55:10.749
You have to study hard
or you'll turn into a drug addict.

750
00:55:10.833 --> 00:55:13.540
Being a good person's more important.

751
00:55:13.625 --> 00:55:16.374
I've never seen thatjug.
Is it from Mexico?

752
00:55:16.458 --> 00:55:18.165
- It's from Cuenca.
- From Peru.

753
00:55:39.625 --> 00:55:41.332
If they come...

754
00:55:42.083 --> 00:55:43.083
"Nuno".

755
00:55:43.500 --> 00:55:46.124
"Nuno! Were you smoking?"

756
00:55:46.583 --> 00:55:48.874
- "No. right?"
- I'll say it was yours...

757
00:55:48.958 --> 00:55:50.999
"This is the sixth time..."

758
00:55:52.666 --> 00:55:55.290
- They know.
- You've been caught before.

759
00:55:55.375 --> 00:55:56.582
Exactly.

760
00:55:56.666 --> 00:55:58.499
- Damn!
- Look!

761
00:55:58.916 --> 00:56:00.540
What is it?

762
00:56:01.666 --> 00:56:02.832
There's a spider.

763
00:56:05.125 --> 00:56:07.415
It's massive.
Look. there's another one.

764
00:56:08.083 --> 00:56:09.540
- I'll burn it.
- Let me see.

765
00:56:09.625 --> 00:56:11.332
Hey! Don't burn it!

766
00:56:11.416 --> 00:56:13.332
- It's a living thing.
- I don't like it.

767
00:56:13.416 --> 00:56:14.999
- I don't care.
- You don't like it?

768
00:56:15.083 --> 00:56:17.290
Look!
Look at it move its legs.

769
00:56:18.083 --> 00:56:19.624
- Get off.
- It's disgusting.

770
00:56:19.708 --> 00:56:22.207
- It won't hurt you.
- Don't!

771
00:56:22.291 --> 00:56:23.999
- Seriously?
- Stop!

772
