1090
01:16:11.291 --> 01:16:12.665
Where have you been?

1091
01:16:12.750 --> 01:16:15.207
Shit. María!
How's it going?

1092
01:16:15.291 --> 01:16:16.874
How's your sister?
How are you?

1093
01:16:18.333 --> 01:16:20.207
I'm just here with my niece.

1094
01:16:20.750 --> 01:16:22.207
Pitu. another round.

1095
01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:26.290
- Nachete's paying. he's doing great.
- I thought as much.

1096
01:20:02.875 --> 01:20:03.875
Marina.

1097
01:20:05.291 --> 01:20:07.165
You see. we weren't dead.

1098
01:20:09.166 --> 01:20:10.957
They just hid us away.

1099
01:21:03.166 --> 01:21:07.707
Don't even think about
reading this diary.

1100
01:21:27.875 --> 01:21:32.165
<i>A rose cries for love</i>

1101
01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:39.415
<i>September 17th. 1983.</i>

1102
01:21:41.916 --> 01:21:45.499
<i>I should know tonnes about sailing
by now. but I'm lazy</i>

1103
01:21:46.041 --> 01:21:49.457
<i>and when I'm on the boat
I love sunbathing.</i>

1104
01:21:49.541 --> 01:21:50.541
<i>But anyway.</i>

1105
01:21:50.625 --> 01:21:53.957
<i>I'm learning something
because Fon teaches me.</i>

1106
01:21:54.041 --> 01:21:55.374
<i>He's a great sailor.</i>

1107
01:22:01.625 --> 01:22:04.332
<i>The flat Fon and I got
is really nice.</i>

1108
01:22:04.416 --> 01:22:06.749
<i>From the bedroom.
we can see the Ria.</i>

1109
01:22:06.833 --> 01:22:10.207
<i>Cangas. Moaña.
the Cíes Islands and the sea.</i>

1110
01:22:10.541 --> 01:22:13.082
<i>Sometimes it's calm. blue. peaceful.</i>

1111
01:22:13.166 --> 01:22:16.374
<i>Sometimes wild. choppy.</i>

1112
01:22:16.833 --> 01:22:18.124
<i>but always the sea.</i>

1113
01:22:18.208 --> 01:22:21.665
<i>And your eyes</i>

1114
01:22:21.750 --> 01:22:26.499
<i>Dig into me</i>

1115
01:22:26.583 --> 01:22:29.415
